</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3116523FFAFA50FCFEBC0C7FC08A771" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB436A8FFAFA50FCFEBC0C7FC08A771" blockId="22.[151,1436,151,338]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="B97FEABAFFAFA50FCFEBC0C7FE7AA692" box="[198,483,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="B97FEABAFFAFA50FCFEBC0C7FEA0A692" bold="true" box="[198,313,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D2BFFAFA50FCE6CC0C8FE7AA692" authorityName="Jousseaume" authorityYear="1872" box="[321,483,152,177]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="bayani">Conus bayani</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is comparatively abundant at Periyakuppam and occurs frequently with 
<emphasis id="B97FEABAFFAFA50FCA10C0C8FEA0A6FA" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D2BFFAFA50FCA10C0C8FF25A6FA" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="amadis">C. amadis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D2BFFAFA50FCFEAC090FEA0A6FA" box="[199,313,192,217]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="monile">C. monile</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D2BFFAFA50FCE5DC090FE64A6FA" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[368,509,192,217]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="betulinus">
<emphasis id="B97FEABAFFAFA50FCE5DC090FE64A6FA" box="[368,509,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">C. betulinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The limited distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D2BFFAFA50FCC6BC090FC2FA6FA" authorityName="Jousseaume" authorityYear="1872" box="[838,950,192,217]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="bayani">
<emphasis id="B97FEABAFFAFA50FCC6BC090FC2FA6FA" box="[838,950,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">C. bayani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the Northern region could be due to its preference for sand bottoms. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A4B59FFAFA50FCEC6C0B8FD18A721" author="Kohn, A. J." box="[491,641,232,258]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="357 - 362" refId="ref43801" refString="Kohn, A. J. (2001) The Conidae of India revisited. Phuket Marine Biological Centre Special Publication, 25, 357 - 362." type="journal article" year="2001">Kohn (2001)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D2BFFAFA50FCC20C0B8FCE6A722" authorityName="Jousseaume" authorityYear="1872" box="[781,895,232,257]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="bayani">
<emphasis id="B97FEABAFFAFA50FCC20C0B8FCE6A722" box="[781,895,232,257]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">C. bayani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a deep-water species. However, at Periyakuppam, this species was found at depths &lt;
<specimenCount id="9D0DFD21FFAFA50FCDA6C140FD57A709" box="[651,718,272,298]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="generic">
<quantity id="4CF39B4DFFAFA50FCDA6C140FD53A709" box="[651,714,272,298]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="m" value="15.0">15 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
Specimens collected at Periyakuppam are larger (
<quantity id="4CF39B4DFFAFA50FCA32C140FAECA709" box="[1311,1397,272,298]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.2" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="mm" value="72.0">72 mm</quantity>
) in shell length than those reported (
<quantity id="4CF39B4DFFAFA50FCD3BC168FDF2A771" box="[534,619,312,338]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="mm" value="65.0">65 mm</quantity>
) by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A4B59FFAFA50FCD8DC168FC14A771" author="Rockel, D. &amp; Korn, W. &amp; Kohn, A. J." box="[672,909,312,338]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="84" refId="ref46330" refString="Rockel, D., Korn, W. &amp; Kohn, A. J. (1995) Manual of the living Conidae. Vol. 1: Indo-Pacific. Christa Hemmen Verlag, Wiesbaden, pp. 516, pl. 84." type="book chapter" year="1995">
Röckel 
<emphasis id="B97FEABAFFAFA50FCDD7C168FCADA772" box="[762,820,312,337]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">et al.</emphasis>
(1995)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
